Arnie schema migrations (Alembic)
=================================

Alembic owns the database schema. The app's SQLAlchemy models in db/models.py are
the source of truth; migrations in alembic/versions/ are the version history that
brings any database up to that schema.

How it's wired
--------------
- alembic/env.py imports the app's Base.metadata (db.database.Base + db.models) and
  reads DATABASE_URL from the environment via db.database._resolve_database_url(), so
  migrations target the same DB the app does. Async drivers are coerced to sync for
  Alembic: sqlite+aiosqlite -> sqlite (pysqlite), postgresql+asyncpg / bare
  postgres:// / postgresql:// -> postgresql+psycopg (psycopg3 is sync-capable).
- alembic.ini's sqlalchemy.url is intentionally blank — env.py supplies it.
- On Render, `alembic upgrade head` runs as the service preDeployCommand (after build,
  before the new instance serves traffic). On Postgres the app's init_db() does NOT
  create_all — Alembic is the only thing that touches schema there.
- Local dev + the in-memory pytest suite use SQLite, where init_db() still runs
  create_all + the legacy db.database._migrate() path. (Slated for retirement once
  fully on Postgres — see AUDIT.md.)

Everyday workflow: you changed db/models.py
--------------------------------------------
1. Generate a migration from the model diff:

     DATABASE_URL='sqlite+aiosqlite:///arnie.db' \
       .venv/bin/python3 -m alembic revision --autogenerate -m "add X to users"

   (Any reachable DB works for autogenerate; a local SQLite file is fine. The diff is
   computed model-vs-DB, then emitted as dialect-agnostic op.* calls.)

2. READ the generated file in alembic/versions/. Autogenerate is a draft, not gospel:
   - It does NOT detect renames (shows as drop+add — fix by hand to avoid data loss).
   - Check server defaults, enum/type changes, and index names.
   - For Postgres data-preserving changes, hand-edit as needed.

3. Verify it round-trips with no drift:

     DATABASE_URL='sqlite+aiosqlite:////tmp/verify.db' .venv/bin/python3 -m alembic upgrade head
     DATABASE_URL='sqlite+aiosqlite:////tmp/verify.db' .venv/bin/python3 -m alembic check
       # -> "No new upgrade operations detected."

   And confirm it compiles for Postgres:

     DATABASE_URL='postgresql+psycopg://u:p@localhost/db' \
       .venv/bin/python3 -m alembic upgrade head --sql | head -40

4. Run the suite (LINKING_ENABLED=true PROACTIVE_MESSAGING_ENABLED=false pytest), commit
   the migration WITH the model change, and push. Render applies it on the next deploy.

Useful commands
---------------
  alembic current              # which revision the DB is on
  alembic history --verbose    # full revision chain
  alembic upgrade head         # apply all pending migrations
  alembic downgrade -1         # roll back one revision (write downgrade() for real reverts)
  alembic check                # fail if models and migrations have drifted (good for CI)

Rules of thumb
--------------
- One migration per schema change, committed alongside the model edit. Never hand-edit
  the DB in prod; never reintroduce ad-hoc ALTERs in db/database.py for Postgres.
- Always write a real downgrade() when feasible so a bad deploy is reversible.
- Baseline revision is fa41393154b3 (down_revision=None) — the full current schema.
